snippet.title: [URDU] 2025 PMWC at EWC Grand Finals D3 | PUBG MOBILE WORLD CUP at ESPORTS WORLD CUP
snippet.description:
🏆 GrandFinals Teesra din | 3rd August.

2025 PUBG MOBILE WORLD CUP jo k ESPORTS WORLD CUP ka stage sajh chuka hai or wo faisly ki ghari aa chuki hai, aaj Grand Finals ka aakhri din hai Riyadh mein, jahan sirf ek team sab par bhaari padegi, taa k wo takht nasheen ho saken aur apna naam PUBG MOBILE ki tareekh mein hamesha ke liye likhwa saken.

Kai dino k intense competition ke baad, duniya ki top ki 16 PUBG MOBILE teamon ne apni jagah banayi hai final stage mein — glory, legacy, aur $3,000,000 ke prize pool ke liye. Yehi wo lamha hai jiske liye har team ne saalon se mehnat ki hai. Group Stage ki best teams aur Survival Stage k champions ab aamne samne honge is saal k sabse dhamakedaar showdown mein. "Teen din, SMASH RULE, aur sirf ek champion."

Safar ka ye aakhri moqa hai — lekin sirf ek team uthayegi trophy aur likhegi apna naam PUBG MOBILE ki tareekh mein. Aakhir kaar Grand Finals ka aghaz hony jaarha hai.

🔥2025 PMWC apko kyu miss nahe krna hai:

Yahan High pressure survival matches horhy hain!
16 teamain, or sirf 8 Grand Finals ka ticket hasil krengi!
Cheer karo apny favorite region aur team ko $3,000,000 prize aur taaj hasil krny k liye!
Grand Finals mein exciting SMASH RULE format hoga!

🔥 SMASH RULE kaise kaam karta hai?

Grand finals mai doosry din ke baad, Match Point Threshold set kiya jaega #1 ranked team ke points +10 add kr k.
Jo team ye points complete karegi, usay trophy jeetne ke liye ek aur match jeetna hoga kisi bad waly match mein. Agar kisi ne threshold match mein hi chicken kr liya to title nahi milega. Agar atharway match tak koi bhi team SMASH Rule se title hasil nahi kar pati, to mayari qawaneen ke mutabiq jis team ke qul adaad zyada honge wo team jeetegi.

📅 TOURNAMENT SCHEDULE

Group Stage: July 25–27
Survival Stage: July 29–30
Grand Finals: August 1–3

snippet.title: The Conjuring: Last Rites | Official Trailer
snippet.description:
Discover why this case ended it all. #TheConjuring: Last Rites - Only in Theaters September 5.

From New Line Cinema comes the ninth entry in the more than $2 billion theatrical Conjuring universe, The Conjuring: Last Rites, directed by franchise veteran Michael Chaves and produced by franchise architects James Wan and Peter Safran.

The Conjuring: Last Rites delivers another thrilling chapter of the iconic Conjuring cinematic universe, based on real events.  Vera Farmiga and Patrick Wilson reunite for one last case as renowned, real-life paranormal investigators Ed and Lorraine Warren in a powerful and spine-chilling addition to the global box office-breaking franchise.

Farmiga and Wilson star alongside Mia Tomlinson and Ben Hardy, who portray Ed and Lorraine’s daughter Judy Warren and her boyfriend, Tony Spera, as well as Steve Coulter returning as Father Gordon, Rebecca Calder, Elliot Cowan, Kíla Lord Cassidy, Beau Gadsdon, John Brotherton and Shannon Kook.

Chaves directs from a screenplay by Ian Goldberg & Richard Naing and David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick, story by David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick & James Wan, based on characters created by Chad Hayes & Carey W. Hayes.  The executive producers are Michael Clear, Judson Scott, Hans Ritter, David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick, Natalia Safran, John Rickard and Michael Chaves.

Chaves is joined behind the camera by his creative team, including director of photography Eli Born, production designer John Frankish, editors Elliot Greenberg and Gregory Plotkin, visual effects supervisor Scott Edelstein, visual effects producer Eric Bruneau and costume designer Graham Churchyard, with casting by Rose Wicksteed and Sophie Kingston-Smith.  The music supervisor is Ian Broucek and the music is by composer Benjamin Wallfisch.

New Line Cinema Presents The Safran Company / An Atomic Monster Production, The Conjuring: Last Rites.  The film will be released worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures and will be only in theaters and IMAX® in North America on September 5, 2025, and internationally beginning 3 September 2025.

snippet.title: [URDU] 2025 PMWC at EWC Grand Finals D1 | PUBG MOBILE WORLD CUP at ESPORTS WORLD CUP
snippet.description:
🏆 GrandFinals Pehla din | 1st August.

2025 PUBG MOBILE WORLD CUP jo k ESPORTS WORLD CUP mai horha hai ab apne aakhri aur sabse bary marhaly mein daakhil ho chuka hai — Grand Finals aaj Riyadh mein shuru ho rahe hain! Behtareen teamain aik dusre ke saamne aayengi, lekin sirf ek hi team champion banegi. Lekin is dafa aik twist hai or wo yeh —k  kya champion ka faisla SMASH RULE se hoga?

Kai dino k intense competition ke baad, duniya ki top ki 16 PUBG MOBILE teamon ne apni jagah banayi hai final stage mein — glory, legacy, aur $3,000,000 ke prize pool ke liye. Yehi wo lamha hai jiske liye har team ne saalon se mehnat ki hai. Group Stage ki best teams aur Survival Stage k champions ab aamne samne honge is saal k sabse dhamakedaar showdown mein. "Teen din, SMASH RULE, aur sirf ek champion."

Safar ka ye aakhri moqa hai — lekin sirf ek team uthayegi trophy aur likhegi apna naam PUBG MOBILE ki tareekh mein. Aakhir kaar Grand Finals ka aghaz hony jaarha hai.

🔥2025 PMWC apko kyu miss nahe krna hai:

Yahan High pressure survival matches horhy hain!
16 teamain, or sirf 8 Grand Finals ka ticket hasil krengi!
Cheer karo apny favorite region aur team ko $3,000,000 prize aur taaj hasil krny k liye!
Grand Finals mein exciting SMASH RULE format hoga!

🔥 SMASH RULE kaise kaam karta hai?

Grand finals mai doosry din ke baad, Match Point Threshold set kiya jaega #1 ranked team ke points +10 add kr k.
Jo team ye points complete karegi, usay trophy jeetne ke liye ek aur match jeetna hoga kisi bad waly match mein. Agar kisi ne threshold match mein hi chicken kr liya to title nahi milega. Agar atharway match tak koi bhi team SMASH Rule se title hasil nahi kar pati, to mayari qawaneen ke mutabiq jis team ke qul adaad zyada honge wo team jeetegi.

Survival Stage: July 29–30

snippet.title: Piya Ghar Aaya - Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan (Asad's Remix)
snippet.description:
All praise to Ustaad Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan.

I'm excited to finally share the full version. Thanks for waiting so patiently (most of you :p)
I'm starting off my new series called EIGHT x EIGHT with this track, As a part of this series I'll put out a new song every Thursday for the next 8 weeks

I grew up in Pakistan, and I now live in Canada. My family is from Faisalabad. Growing up, my grandfather listened to a lot of qawwali around me as a kid and that influence never left my dna. After years of making music, I finally did something with a track from Ustaad Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan. I also really enjoyed seeing videos of this track from all over the world, specially from home - thank you for sharing those. 

This remix blew up on TikTok, Instagram etc but more importantly, as you can see in this video, it created a beautiful moment for a group of people and that's what music is all about. Ustaad Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan's legacy continues to serve moments like this, I'm grateful to have been a vessel. 

Thanks for showing this so much love, lots more music soon

Asad 
-
